TI  - An Empirical Analysis of the Unionization of Foreign Manufacturing Firms in the U.S.
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 119
EP  - 132
VL  - 21
IS  - 1
AB  - The ability of American labor unions to organize workers in majority and wholly foreign-owned manufacturing plants in the U.S. is examined by analyzing union representation election results. The principal conclusions are that the nationality of a firm is not a significant factor influencing election outcomes and that foreign firms are as difficult to unionize as domestic American firms. Several reasons are offered to explain these findings.
