DA  - 1990/03/01
TI  - Firm Ownership Preferences and Host Government Restrictions: An Integrated Approach
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 1
EP  - 22
VL  - 21
IS  - 1
AB  - Two approaches may explain how multinational enterprises (MNEs) select ownership structures for subsidiaries. The first argues that MNEs prefer structures that minimize that transaction costs of doing business abroad. The second argues that ownership structures are determined by negotiations with host governments, whose outcomes depend on the bargaining power of the firm. This paper presents a framework integrating these two approaches and uses statistical methods to separate their effects empirically.
