SP  - 95
EP  - 117
VL  - 21
IS  - 1
AB  - The major rating agencies assign quality rating to international security offerings. These ratings serve as indicators of perceived sovereign risk associated with such offerings. A review of the ratings process followed by the major rating agencies (in particular, the Standard & Poor's Corporation) reveals that ratings are assigned with considerable reliance on informal judgment. Informal judgmental systems, however, can induce serious inconsistencies in the relative importance assigned to criteria used in assigning rating and lead to biased ratings.
